President Barack Obama has announced the appointment of a Presidential Delegation to the Federal Republic of Germany to attend the Organization for Security and Cooperation in Europe Berlin Conference on Anti-Semitism Tenth Anniversary Commemoration. The delegation will be led by Samantha Power, the U.S. Permanent Representative to the United Nations. Other members of the delegation include John B. Emerson, the U.S. Ambassador to Germany, Daniel Baer, the U.S. Permanent Representative to the Organization of Security and Cooperation in Europe, Melissa Rogers, Special Assistant to the President and Executive Director of The White House Office of Faith-Based Partnerships, Ira N. Forman, Special Envoy to Monitor and Combat Anti-Semitism, Deborah Lipstadt, Member of the U.S. Holocaust Memorial Council and Dorot Professor of Modern Jewish and Holocaust Studies at Emory University, and Abraham H. Foxman, National Director of the Anti-Defamation League.